						<summary>

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1238, Naḷa, Phālguṇa, śu. 5, Guruvāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1317 February 17,</hi> Thursday, when <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēsvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tiparasa,</hi> stated to be the son of the Hoysaḷa king <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Ballāḷadēva (III),</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Bhairavadēvarasa</hi> granted land at ? <hi rend="bold">Hāluviḍi</hi> as <hi rend="italic">koḍagi</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Masaṇaseṭṭi</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kariyamaṟe,</hi> who was the head of merchants.</p>						

						</summary>
